== English ==

=== Pronunciation ===

* {{IPA|/frī'ə-bəl/}}

=== Etymology ===

* Latin friābilis, from friāre, to crumble.

=== Adjective ===
'''friable'''

# Easily broken into small [[fragment]]s, [[crumble]]d, or reduced to [[powder]].
# (''of soil'') loose and large-grained in consistency.

